Buttermilk Waffles
  --Cook's Illustrated
  
1 c ap flour
1 tbsp cornmeal (optional)
1/2 tsp salt
1 tsp baking soda
1 egg separated
7/8 c buttermilk
2 tbsp unsalted butter, melted

Heat waffle iron. Whisk dry ingredients togerther in a medium bowl. Whisk yolk with buttermilk and butter. Beat egg white until it just holds a 2" peak. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients in a thin steady stream while gently mixing with a rubber spatula; be careful not to add liquid faster than you can incorporate it. Toward end of mixing, use a folding motion to incorporate ingredients; gently fold in egg whites. Spread appropriate amount of batter onto iron. Following manufacturer's instructions, cook waffle until golden brown, 2-5 min. Serve immediately.

